implement the inner host target selection algorithm we improve the vm clone process by encouraging more clones inside the same host. The metric Scarcity as we
named, is to measure the urgency a host needs a clone. The scarcity basically evaluates how many rounds of
clone process is required to complete the cloning process for all nodes on that host.

The targetSelector is implemented as Strategy pattern in FastCloneService, i.e., you can inject different
selection algorithms based on your needs.

bug fix in disk-failure-handling - copy mac address from parent vm to fix data disk loss, we create an empty VM and attach system disks from parent vm.
If the mac address for the new vm is a new one, then linux probably will rename eth0
to eth1 according to udev rules, and thus our network initialization script will fail.
In this fix, we copied the mac address of parent vm to prevent the eth rename issue.
